---
import DocLayout from '../../layouts/DocLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL || '/storyhouse-design-system/';
const currentPath = `${base}guides/getting-started`;
---

<DocLayout
  title="Getting Started"
  description="Install the Storyhouse design system and start building with production-ready components."
  currentPath={currentPath}
>
  <section>
    <h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>
    <p>Install the packages you need via npm. The design system is distributed as multiple packages within the <code>@storyhouse</code> scope.</p>

    <CodeBlock lang="bash" title="Terminal" code={`npm install @storyhouse/components @storyhouse/tokens`} />

    <p>Or install individually if you only need specific packages:</p>

    <CodeBlock lang="bash" title="Terminal" code={`# Core components
npm install @storyhouse/components

# Design tokens (colors, typography, spacing)
npm install @storyhouse/tokens

# Utility helpers
npm install @storyhouse/utils`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="peer-dependencies">Peer Dependencies</h2>
    <p>
      The design system requires <code>react</code> and <code>react-dom</code> v18+ as peer dependencies.
      Make sure they're installed in your project:
    </p>

    <CodeBlock lang="bash" title="Terminal" code={`npm install react react-dom`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="basic-usage">Basic Usage</h2>
    <p>Once installed, import and use components directly in your React application:</p>

    <CodeBlock title="app.tsx" code={`import { Button, Card, Badge, Avatar } from '@storyhouse/components';
import '@storyhouse/tokens/tokens.css'; // Import design tokens

function App() {
  return (
    <Card>
      <div className="flex items-center gap-4">
        <Avatar name="Jane Doe" />
        <div>
          <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold">Welcome to Storyhouse</h2>
          <p className="text-gray-600">
            Your design system is ready to use.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div className="mt-4 flex gap-2">
        <Button variant="primary">Get Started</Button>
        <Button variant="ghost">Learn More</Button>
      </div>
    </Card>
  );
}`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="css-tokens">Importing CSS Tokens</h2>
    <p>
      Design tokens are available as CSS custom properties. Import <code>@storyhouse/tokens/tokens.css</code>
      in your app's entry point to make all tokens available globally:
    </p>

    <CodeBlock title="main.tsx" code={`import React from 'react';
import ReactDOM from 'react-dom/client';
import App from './App';
import '@storyhouse/tokens/tokens.css';

ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root')!).render(
  <React.StrictMode>
    <App />
  </React.StrictMode>
);`} />

    <p>Once imported, you can use tokens in your CSS:</p>

    <CodeBlock lang="css" title="styles.css" code={`.my-element {
  color: var(--color-brand-orange-500);
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  padding: var(--spacing-4);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
}`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="tailwind-config">Tailwind CSS Configuration</h2>
    <p>
      If you use Tailwind CSS, extend your config to use the design system tokens:
    </p>

    <CodeBlock lang="js" title="tailwind.config.js" code={`/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
export default {
  content: [
    './src/**/*.{ts,tsx}',
    './node_modules/@storyhouse/components/**/*.{ts,tsx}',
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        brand: {
          50: '#fff7ed',
          100: '#ffedd5',
          200: '#fed7aa',
          300: '#fdba74',
          400: '#fb923c',
          500: '#f97316',
          600: '#ea580c',
          700: '#c2410c',
          800: '#9a3412',
          900: '#7c2d12',
        },
      },
      fontFamily: {
        sans: ['Inter', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'],
        mono: ['JetBrains Mono', 'monospace'],
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [],
};`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="project-structure">Project Structure</h2>
    <p>
      The design system monorepo is organized as follows:
    </p>

    <CodeBlock lang="text" title="Directory Layout" code={`packages/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ components/    # React component library
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Button
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Card
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Input
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Badge
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ Avatar
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ tokens/        # Design tokens (CSS + JS)
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ colors
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ typography
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ spacing
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ shadows
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ utils/         # Shared utilities
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ docs/          # Documentation site (Astro)
в””в”Ђв”Ђ storybook/     # Interactive component playground`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="next-steps">Next Steps</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Browse the <a href={`${base}components`}>component library</a> to see what's available</li>
      <li>Learn about the <a href={`${base}guides/utilities`}>cn() utility</a> for class merging with Tailwind</li>
      <li>Explore <a href={`${base}tokens`}>design tokens</a> for colors, typography, and spacing</li>
      <li>Visit the <a href={`${base}storybook/`}>Storybook</a> for interactive component previews</li>
      <li>Read the <a href={`${base}guides/theming`}>theming guide</a> to customize the system</li>
      <li>Review the <a href={`${base}guides/contributing`}>contributing guide</a> to add new components</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</DocLayout>
